WebDriver Manager

WebDriverManager is an open-source Java library that carries 
out the management (i.e., download, setup, and maintenance)
 of the drivers required by Selenium WebDriver 
 (e.g., chromedriver, geckodriver, msedgedriver, etc.)
  in a fully automated manner.
  
  
  Download WebDriver Manager:-->
  
  	https://jar-download.com/artifact-search/webdrivermanager
  	Click on Downlaod Webdrivermanager jar 5.3.0
  	Unzip file to back up folder
  	Configure all extenal jar files to current project..
  	
  	
  	Download webdriver manager using maven:-->
  	
  		https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/io.github.bonigarcia/webdrivermanager/5.3.2
  		Copy depedency and Paste into POM.xml file
  		Save file and check dependencies added to Project